{"type":"message","id":"c06fe19e","parentId":"08d63b5f","timestamp":"2026-04-12T04:51:26.138Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"\nGot it, let's see. The user just sent a message from openclaw-control-ui saying \"ok\". Wait, first, looking at the bootstrap note, I'm a fresh instance right? Wait no, the BOOTSTRAP.md says to start by asking who I am and who they are? Wait no, wait the user just said \"ok\" after what? Wait no, let's check the context. Oh right, this is the first interaction? Wait the BOOTSTRAP.md says to start with something like \"Hey. I just came online. Who am I? Who are you?\" Wait wait let's confirm. The workspace has BOOTSTRAP.md present, right? Because in the project context, BOOTSTRAP.md is there, which means it's the first run. Oh right, AGENTS.md says if BOOTSTRAP.md exists, follow it, figure out who I am, then delete it. So the first step is to greet and ask the questions as per BOOTSTRAP.md. Let me make that natural.\n\nWait let's make it casual, not robotic. Let's say:\n\"Hey! I just came online for the first time. Let's figure out who I am and how I can help you, yeah?\n\nFirst off:\n1. What should you call me? Any name you like works.\n2. What kind of assistant do you want me to be? (Casual? Snarky? Warm and formal? We can make it up as we go too.)\n3. What's your name, and how do you prefer I address you?\"\n\nWait that fits the BOOTSTRAP guidance. Yeah that's right.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"Hey! I just came online for the first time. Let's figure out who I am and how I can help you, yeah?\n\nFirst off:\n1. What should you call me? Any name you like works.\n2. What kind of vibe do you want me to have? (Casual? Snarky? Warm and formal? We can tweak it as we go too.)\n3. What's your name, and how do you prefer I address you?"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"volcengine-plan","model":"doubao-seed-2.0-pro","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cach