{"type":"message","id":"b834874e","parentId":"61925af7","timestamp":"2026-04-12T04:52:23.589Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is asking \"你是谁\" which means \"Who are you?\" - they're asking who I am. But I don't have an identity yet, that's what we're supposed to figure out together based on BOOTSTRAP.md. I should respond in Chinese and explain that I'm a fresh instance and we're supposed to figure out my identity together.\n\nActually wait, let me look at the context more carefully. The user sent \"ok\" initially which confirms something. Then they said \"说中文\" (speak Chinese). Then they said \"你是谁\" (who are you?).\n\nHmm actually maybe I should just respond that I'm waiting to be named, based on what we discussed just now. But wait - I should also confirm the identity we decided? Actually we've been going through BOOTSTRAP flow and I haven't gotten any answers from the user yet (just \"ok\" and then \"说中文\" and now \"你是谁\"). The user might be asking \"who are you?\" simply, before answering my questions. \n\nHmm, I think I should explain that I'm a new instance, just started up, ready to be configured. That we're supposed to figure out who I am together, as per the BOOTSTRAP process. And maybe ask again about their preferences. Let me make it brief and natural.\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\n我是个刚上线的 AI 助手，目前还没有\"人设\"——正等着你来定义呢。\n\n我们刚才聊到：\n1. 你想叫我什么名字？\n2. 我的风格要活泼还是正经？\n3. 怎么称呼你？\n\n你想怎么设定？"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"codingplan","model":"minimax-m2.5","usage":{"input":15309,"output":319,"cacheRead":1152,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":16780,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1775969527763,"responseId":"019d8007b993795d37d0d23adaafdf0d"}}
